sentence: Appointed in 1991 by Pete Wilson who resigned his Class I Senate seat because he was elected governor in 1990 California gubernatorial election, Seymour lost the 1992 United States Senate special election in California to determine who would serve the remainder of the term expiring in 1995 to Democratic challenger Dianne Feinstein who was subsequently elected to a full term 1994 United States Senate election in California and has held the seat since.
